<br>
I freely admit that my 1hs weapons suck as I put all my money into getting a Stonebladed Axe of Dismay (paid 10K - Woot).<br>
<br>
Currently using a Tae Ew sword (8 1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  in primary and Jarsath Trident in secondary. I also have a spiked club.<br>
<br>
My 2hs is only 156 atm and I am working on it.<br>
<br>
Have read that for xp groups (and I never tend to go on raids) my new Axe should hold taunt ok, but atm this is not the case.<br>
<br>
What should I do?<br>
<br>
Options seem to be:<br>
<br>
1) Sell axe and buy another Frosty/CotIO which was my previous 1hs combo.<br>
<br>
2) Train up 2hs and hope that with higher skill I will dish more dmg and keep the taunt.<br>
<br>
Btw, I have around 2K cash to spend, but doubt that Lammy or Jade Mace would be much better than my current primary.<br>
<br>
It was the Rogue I keep losing the agro to; they were BSing for around 460 frequently.<br>
<br>
Prefer to keep my new axe if I can, but any suggestions gratefully received.<br>
<br>
Rathsar Ironforge<br>
51 Champion<br>
CoP<br>
Lanys T'vyl <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhaass.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haass</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 518<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/1/02 4:17:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4051.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Probs holding aggro with poor 1hs weapons</span><hr size=1> None of that crap is gonna help you as a 51 to hold aggro against a 56 rogue.  Think about why for a minute and you should be able to figure out what you have to do...and it doesn't require you to get any new gear. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48986">Haass Wolvesbane</a> <BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71943">Cagna Soulshaker</a> 

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/urathsar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rathsar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/1/02 4:32:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4051.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Probs holding aggro with poor 1hs weapons</span><hr size=1> Been using taunt all the time and trying to keep totally in the mobs face.<br>
<br>
I honestly can't think of anything else, unless you mean get my levels and weapon skills up?<br>
<br>
While you are listening Haass, is it worth my while getting a Jouneyman's Walking stick at my level?<br>
<br>
I often find that the proc from my ToD gets resisted in ME and wondered if a JWS might help with this.<br>
<br>
Rath <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/urathsar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rathsar</A> at: 10/1/02 4:39:54 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usterix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sterix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/1/02 5:51:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4051.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Probs holding aggro with poor 1hs weapons</span><hr size=1> You will have to have very good weapons in order to keep aggro from 5 levels higher rogue, unless rogue helps you a lot in it, using worse weapons and keeping attack off in addition to evading.<br>
<br>
In aggro, levels&gt;weapons in most cases.<br>
<br>
And also, weapon skill effects a lot, max that 2hs skill and I think you will be able to keep aggro in most cases. ME is not an easy place though, most mobs are very high level, I find they ignore my taunt (what taunt?) too often even at 60.<br>
 <p>Sterix<BR>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=34908>Gnome Warlord</a><BR>
<a href=http://pub32.ezboard.com/bvitamaeternam>Co-Leader of Vitam Aeternam of Povar</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/urathsar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rathsar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/1/02 6:25:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4051.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Probs holding aggro with poor 1hs weapons</span><hr size=1> Thanks Sterix, I am by no means an experienced Warrior (albeit this is my main) and I really appreciate your open, honest and easily understandible reply.<br>
<br>
Will max 2hs as soon as I possibly can.<br>
<br>
XP in Umbral seems better than ME (when I can get a group) and I could do with a few bits of the no drop armour from there too.<br>
<br>
Great fun when they rampage too - never experienced it until my first group in Umbral. <br>
<br>
Rathsar moves swiftly to the rear of the mob, as in very - LOL.<br>
