<br>
:P<br>
<br>
Seriously though, heh, I thought Warriors in their 50s couldn't taunt mobs that were even con or higher? If so, that could also be affecting your aggro issues in Maiden's Eye, as a lot of those mobs are yellow or red at 51.<br>
<br>
-Wu<br>
The guy who drops mobs off at Sterix's little feet. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usterix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sterix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/1/02 10:49:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4051.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I can taunt!</span><hr size=1> That is true, taunt will do nothing for even or higher cons before level 60.<br>
At 60 you can taunt...umm..correct me if I am wrong, mobs of max level 63?<br>
<br>
Depending on what you hunted in ME, you couldn't taunt them with taunt button at all.<br>
Toilers and goranga gatherers should be blue for 51, but others mostly higher. <p>Sterix<BR>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=34908>Gnome Warlord</a><BR>
<a href=http://pub32.ezboard.com/bvitamaeternam>Co-Leader of Vitam Aeternam of Povar</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usterix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sterix</A> at: 10/1/02 10:49:59 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utrayvar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trayvar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/1/02 11:31:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4051.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I can taunt!</span><hr size=1> &quot;I find they ignore my taunt (what taunt?) too often even at 60.&quot;<br>
<br>
Tell me about heh.  There are a few places where taunt seems to be purposely toned down.  Haven't run my little test in Cazic Thule again since the supposed change to the tuant skill there, but from what hunts I've had there the last time it sure seems like it's only partially working.<br>
<br>
Test being, get an invis, walk up to a mob, and tuant it.  You'll most likely have to tuant repeatedly since the skill fails a lot (just a percentage chance roll to see whether you taunted or didn't... fail the roll and nothing happens at all, win the roll and you're on the aggro list and the mob attacks you).<br>
<br>
When I did this in CT, before the tuant skill was fixed there, out of 30 tuant button presses that lizard never aggroed on me.  He just stood there calmly at his spawn location the entire time, didn't even know I was there because of invis.  Verdict?  Tuant was completely disabled in that zone at the time I did that.  Could press the key till you were blue in the face (which is what I basically did) and it would never successfully win the roll.<br>
<br>
Most mobs everywhere that I've done this to took 1 to 5 presses to aggro them.  Averaging around 2 presses.  It wouldn't suprise me one bit if the number of presses in ME, and a few other places, were a bit higher.<br>
<br>
I haven't run the test in the Plane of Sky yet, but would like to the next time I'm there.  Everytime that I've been there I could have sworn the tuant skill did nothing to the 51+ mobs there also (which would make sense, since it's an old world engine containing mobs that are 51+... just like Cazic was before they had to change it).  The level 50 thunder spirits were the only mobs that I can remember turning to me with consistancy upon most taunt presses.  The other mobs are all 51+. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubinnamar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Binnamar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 136<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/1/02 1:36:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4051.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I can taunt!</span><hr size=1> Let the 2 mage pets tank. Send them in one at a time wait a second and just run in there and bash the mob. The pets will (maybe not anymore after some patches) hold agro and you won't get hit. Works like a charm, as long as the mage/cleric can keep the pets healed. <p>Binnamar- 51 dwarven warrior<BR>
Kakash- 5 Vah Shir Beastlord<BR>
Tarrew Marr<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhaass.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haass</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 521<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/1/02 2:21:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4051.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I can taunt!</span><hr size=1> Heh, apparantly it wasn't so obvious.<br>
<br>
Yes, I mean level up.  You're just not going to hold aggro over an offensive melee 5 levels higher than you without him gimping his damage so much that it slows the group down considerably.  The issue is not so much which weapons you choose at this point, it's the fact that your skills are lower than his, which means you connect with the mob less, which means you do less damage, which means the mob cares less about you and more about the guy poking him in the back.<br>
<br>
You can have all the taunt weaponry in the world on ya, but when someone is outdamaging you that badly, mobs are never going to stay on you long.  Level up and the problem will go away by itself by virtue of better skills, and you'll also earn more money in that time frame to upgrade your weapons as well. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48986">Haass Wolvesbane</a> <BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71943">Cagna Soulshaker</a> 

